name: jungletrain.net promomix summer 2021
comment:
jungletrain.net is proud to present: Darkstar - jungletrain.net promomix summer 2021

Your personal breakbeat sherpa this summer is Darkstar, back with his fourth Jungletrain promomix installment. The trailhead for this journey is a deep halftime vibe that touches on some esoteric thinkin' music before launching headfirst into amen-laden jungle.

The subdued choppage provides a vibrant plateau of barely contained energy through the majority of the mix, painting a backdrop of a diverse tapestry that enshrouds the skyline that is our musical home. Concluding the the trek, our path winds down towards a cerebral multidimensional meditation guided by modern production techniques that fertilize the rhythmic soil for future generations to contemplate.

Wrapping up, Darkstar adds: "My favorite moment in the mix has to be Aeon Four's Babylon into Rumbleton's Sound Family. The Maya Angelou 'Still I Rise' quotation fits so perfectly in the spacious dubwise breakdown, with the messages interleaving on multiple levels. Recognize and process the past to improve our collective future. One life, one love. Thanks for listening."

We hope you enjoy this summer's promomix, and if you do, make sure to check out Rinse & Repeat Radio every tuesday night from 17.00 - 19.00 PDT, 20.00 - 22.00 EDT, 01.00 - 03.00 BST, 02.00 - 04.00 CEST!

We're taking a short break this summer, see you back in September for the next promomix! Stay safe and Buddha Bless!

Links:
https://rinseandrepeatradio.com/
https://recondnb.net/

--

name: Traktorized: july 2011
comment:
Downloaded from http://official.fm/tracks/277729

 This months mixed bag of 21 tracks starts in the vein of UR003 with Boddika’s “Electron” on Swamp 81, gets beefy with the Solaris Series on Hidden Hawaii, Developer & Surgeon, groovey with Martyn & Mike Slott, another Shed-produced hit on Wax before taking you to the burnt-plastic smell of Morphosis on Aroy Dee’s imprint M>O>S recordings (awesome Carpenter-ish-cinematic-dance-music longplayer there!).

While Addison Groove’s “Work it” already implies to deal with some DJ Funk-alike bounce you get the full booty jerk by Pearson Sound featuring Rod Lee. In between: the new Sandwell District release by Rrose, Sigha on James Ruskin’s Blueprint, the new Martian on Red Planet (whoo-hoo!), Hardfloor feat. ERP, Mike Dehnert’s discovery Roman Lindau and Silent Servants almost hidden track on Developers album “Entrada”. I finally got to play one of those epic journeys by Brendon Moellers alter ego Echologist from ‘Subterranean‘ alongside with Speedy Js tool ‘Shoegaze’ on Electric Deluxe. These two: perfect match – BOMB!

After all, last months fave ‘CLK Recovery’ by Objekt (one of my few vinyl purchases this year), another Sigha track, BiceP’s ‘Washing machine’-sounding freebie ‘Silk’ and last not least Kirk Degiorgio’s take on Martin Buttrich’s ‘Full Clip‘.

name: Traktorized: june 2011
comment:
Downloaded from http://official.fm/tracks/258735

 So this is where it starts again… The plethora of fresh tunes during the last weeks was quite something. Be it Delsin’s Conforce with his trance-alike ‘Vulcan’, Max Cavallera’s beast ‘Hellboys rising’ or that synth powered Boddika track – there’s no shortage of good electronic dance music in sight. This months archive picks: KiNK’s 303-monster ‘Shockwaves’ and the Advent’s ‘Visualize’.

The downloads at XLR8R were quite a good source this month. And props to Speedy J for keeping up releasing all those tools’n'edits on Electric Deluxe. ‘Vulcan’ + ‘Trails edit’ on top – magic.
